# data-testid Convention

Every interactive UI element MUST have a `data-testid` attribute for test automation stability.

## Naming Pattern

```
{screen}-{element-type}-{identifier}
```

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Page container | `{screen}-page` | `login-page` |
| Form | `{screen}-form` | `login-form` |
| Input | `{screen}-input-{field}` | `login-input-email` |
| Button | `{screen}-btn-{action}` | `login-btn-submit` |
| Link | `{screen}-link-{target}` | `sidebar-link-scenarios` |
| Table | `{screen}-table` | `scenarios-table` |
| Row | `{screen}-row-{id}` | `scenarios-row-{s.id}` |
| Checkbox | `{screen}-check-{name}` | `scenarios-check-{s.id}` |
| Select | `{screen}-select-{name}` | `requirements-select-priority` |
| Alert | `{screen}-alert-{type}` | `login-alert-error` |
| Heading | `{screen}-heading` | `scenarios-heading` |

## Rules

1. Use kebab-case for all testid values
2. Dynamic IDs use template literals: `` data-testid={`scenarios-row-${s.id}`} ``
3. Screen name = route segment (login, projects, scenarios, flows, executions, approvals, regression, import)
4. Global elements use: `sidebar-*`, `header-*`, `user-menu-*`
5. Never use CSS classes or Tailwind utilities as locators — they break on styling changes
6. `Button`, `Input` components pass `data-testid` via `...props` spread — just add the prop

## Example

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<Button data-testid="scenarios-btn-new">Yeni senaryo</Button>
<Input data-testid="login-input-email" placeholder="ornek@sirket.com" />
<tr data-testid={`scenarios-row-${s.id}`}>

// ❌ BAD — no testid on interactive element
<Button>Kaydet</Button>
<input type="text" />

// ❌ BAD — wrong naming
<Button data-testid="btn1">
<Input data-testid="emailField">
```
